# 🌸 Iris Flower Classification (OIBSIP Task 1)

This project is a Machine Learning model that classifies iris flowers into three species based on their measurements.

## 📌 Problem Statement
Iris flower has three species:
- Setosa
- Versicolor
- Virginica

The goal is to train a machine learning model that can learn from the measurements of iris flowers and accurately classify them into their respective species.

---

## 🚀 Technologies Used
- Python 🐍
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib (for visualization)

---

## 📊 Dataset
The dataset contains measurements of iris flowers:
- Sepal Length
- Sepal Width
- Petal Length
- Petal Width

You can use:
- Built-in dataset from Scikit-learn  
OR  
- Download dataset manually

---

## ⚙️ Model Used
- K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

---

## 📈 Steps Performed
1. Loaded the dataset
2. Split data into training and testing sets
3. Trained the KNN model
4. Predicted results on test data
5. Evaluated model accuracy

---

## ✅ Output
- Model Accuracy: ~90%+ (approx)

---

